The paper deals with denoising of two-dimensional data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and image processing (cs.MM). The use of quadtree decomposition and space-filling curves suggests a focus on efficient algorithms and data structures, which are often studied in computer science theory (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method compared to a genie that has access to the underlying noiseless data, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) for evaluating the effectiveness of a model.
